<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>1-1231.16</num>
  <heading>Official seal.</heading>
  <para>
    <num>(a)</num>
    <text>The official seal of a notary public in the District shall:</text>
    <para>
      <num>(1)</num>
      <text>Include the following:</text>
      <para>
        <num>(A)</num>
        <text>The notary public's name, exactly stated on the commission;</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(B)</num>
        <text>The words "District of Columbia";</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(C)</num>
        <text>The commission expiration date; and</text>
      </para>
      <para>
        <num>(D)</num>
        <text>Other information required by the Mayor; and</text>
      </para>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>(2)</num>
      <text>Be capable of being copied together with the record to which it is affixed or attached or with which it is logically associated.</text>
    </para>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(b)</num>
    <text>The Mayor shall issue rules regarding the size and form of the seal.</text>
  </para>
